<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/11–244</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-02">November 2,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>As you know, the Russians have recently granted us permission to transport
                        500 trucks across Russia to China. I recommend that you personally cable
                        Marshal Stalin,<note n="29" xml:id="d722fn29">Iosif Vissarionovich Stalin,
                            Chairman of the Council of Commissars of the Soviet Union.</note> asking
                        permission to transport a further 500 trucks per month over Russian
                        territory for China.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>